377 §35-21-14
378 (a) If no timely appeal is filed, the circuit court,
379 upon a quiet title petition by the complainant, shall enter an
380 order enforcing the final administrative order no later than
381 30 days from the filing date of the quiet title petition
382 without further evidentiary hearing or procedural delay. The
383 court may waive the filing fees and court costs for good cause
384 shown. The enforcement order shall:
385 (1) Declare the fraudulent conveyance or attempted
386 conveyance void;
387 (2) Direct the judge of probate to remove or nullify
388 any recorded instrument that clouds title or conflicts with
389 the administrative order; and
390 (3) Quiet title in favor of the rightful real property
391 owner.
